        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Summary"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Adversarial testing for agents combines three complementary techniques: manual red-teaming for creative, open-ended exploration; automated fuzzing for high-volume coverage of mutation variants; and property-based testing for formal verification of invariants. All three must extend to multi-turn scenarios, because the most dangerous agentic attacks build across a conversation rather than arriving in a single prompt. Findings feed back into a regression suite that runs in CI on every change to the agent, its tools, or its system prompt."
          }
        ]
      }
